article.description: Omar Samhan had 16 points and 11 rebounds as St. Mary's beat San Diego 65-42 Thursday for its 15th straight win.
article.shortLinkText: Samhan extends St. Mary's win streak to 15
article.headline: Saint Mary's runs NCAA-best win streak to 15 straight
article.linkText: Samhan extends St. Mary's win streak to 15

inlines.body:
Fast Facts

• The Gaels extended the nation's longest active win streak to 15 games, led by Omar Samhan's 16 points and 11 rebounds.

• The win snapped a two-game losing streak at San Diego, improving St. Mary's to 6-0 on the road this season.

• The loss ended the San Diego's six-game win streak, scoring its fewest points in a game since an 82-39 loss to Utah in December of 2003.

-- ESPN research

article.story: SAN DIEGO -- Omar Samhan had 16 points and 11 rebounds as St. Mary's (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, Unranked AP) beat San Diego 65-42 Thursday for its 15th straight win. St. Mary's (18-1, 5-0 West Coast Conference) opened the game with a 17-4 run, led by 18 at halftime and never looked back. San Diego (12-8, 4-1) shot 32 percent compared to the Gaels' 55.6 percent. Patrick Mills, an Australian Olympian, scored 10 of his 12 points in the first half as St. Mary's built a 32-14 halftime lead and led by as many as 24 in the second half. DeJon Jackson led San Diego with 16 points and Trumaine Johnson added 11. St. Mary's has the nation's longest active win streak. San Diego's six-game losing streak was snapped.
